title: [DesireGrandSubPrix] Kamen Rider Geats - 01-05 [WEB-DL][1080p]
description:
ENTRY! 
------
##
Welcome back to the **Desire Grand Sub Prix**! (Also known as the *DGSP* or _Fansubbing Grand Prix_.) 

A lot has happened since we last checked in! **DeezNuts** and **InoueQuality** have left the game* after Rounds Two and One respectively, and a late entry, **IzuSubs**, has joined! Some records from Round One have even been retroactively altered by the game's administrators!

We now have four main players in this game: **GenmCorp**, **EXCITE!**, **IzuSubs**, and **RTA** (subs are muxed in that order)**. All will continue to fight to the death in a Prime Video stage to shape the world to their liking.

Pretense-aside once again, the each primary softsub (thus far) has been rounded up and remuxed onto Prime Video-sourced files with more than twice the bitrate of the TTFC encodes. Also included are the JP captions tracks and audio commentary tracks (no translations available at the moment). Pick your poison. 

--
#### **Notes:
As you may know, Episode 1 was retroactively edited from the broadcast version to remove the Hellboy mask. For the sake of preservation, Episode 1 has been v2'ed using the editions feature of the Matroska format. The revised version is now the default track, but the broadcast version is available as an alternate title. If your player doesn't respect editions, the original clip _should_ play at the end of the file.

For Episodes 1 and 2, DeezNuts is still available as subtitle track 6. For Episode 1, InoueQuality is still available as subtitle track 7.

Edit: It appears InoueQuality is not entirely out of the game, we'll see if they can make it into any future rounds!

Greetings from the Gentlemen of Hàn!

This is our english fansub batch release of **_Episodes 32 to 39_** of the _**1994’s Romance of the Three Kingdoms.**_ It comprises of the first full arc of the series, titled _**“赤壁鏖战”**_ or _**“Battle of Red Cliffs”.**_  This is part 2 of the "Battle of Red Cliffs," the arc's finale and in some sense the "true" opening prologue of the Three Kingdoms period, as lines will start to be drawn beginning from here.
As before, please read our previous Foreword for extra context on the history of this production, the novel, and of the history it is based on:
https://pastebin.com/naC3tXAP

- **Title:** Okusama wa Majo (also known as "Bewitched in Tokyo")
- **Native Title:** 奥さまは魔女
- **Episodes:** 11 + SP
- **Broadcast Network:** TBS
- **Release Date:** January 16 - March 26, 2004
- **Theme Songs:** "Magic In Your Eyes" by *Tommy February6*, "One True Love" by *10,000 Promises*,
"My Sweet Home" by *10,000 Promises*.
- **English Softsubs** by: [**kowaihitotachi**](https://www.d-addicts.com/forums/viewtopic.php?t=163178). No subtitles are currently available for the SP.

**Synopsis**

The wife is a witch! But she likes humans, and she loves her husband. Arisa (Yonekura Ryoko) is fascinated by humans. So much so that she leaves the magic world. But the broom she uses is faulty, and she winds up in Japan. There she meets Joji Matsui (Harada Taizo), who works at an advertising agency. Joji has been assigned by his boss Ichio Suzuki (Takenaka Naoto) the difficult task of winning over Shiori Nomo (Ishikawa Asami), who is in charge of corporate communications at a client. However, a little word from Arisa helps Joji win over Shiori, and his agency gets the opportunity to pitch. Arisa and Joji fall in love and marry. Arisa swears never to use magic again as she and Joji begin their strange witch/human married life. However, Arisa's mother, Daria (Natsuki Mari), wants to take Arisa back to her world and uses magic to be a nuisance to the new couple. Arisa has to take care of Joji's boss Suzuki who drops in all the time, the prying eyes of their neighbors and the interference of her witch mother.

This is a Japanese remake of the classic 1964 American sitcom, [**"Bewitched"**](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0057733/)

title: [Weeaboo-Shogun] Special Rescue Exceedraft 39
description:
SPECIAL RESCUE EXCEEDRAFT
Episode 39
"Swing Away! The Promised Hardball"

A boy named Naoki is on the verge of giving up baseball, but a drifter teaches him the proper way to swing and promises to be at his district tournament. But when he goes missing, the boy is disheartened and concerned. Meanwhile, Exceedraft is investigating a jewel theft using a powerful laser weapon. When these two incidents come crashing together and Kosaku and the drifter and abducted, it's up to Kosaku to set things right. 

NOTES:
This is the last Kyoko Sagiyama episode in the Rescue Police trilogy, and after years of me making fun of her weird interest in including magic stuffed animals and psychic girls in a supercop show, I am pleased to say that finally, in her last episode in the trilogy, she knocks it out of the park, no pun intended. This is a very slickly written episode that, again, no pun intended, covers all its bases. 

A few items of interest: 
When Naoki is telling Kosaku about how Yasu trained him, notice the sad music that plays during the flashback. That's not Exceedraft music -- that's Solbrain's theme!
At 19:02, notice the traffic backed up on the loop exit in the background. Wonder if they saw them filming the series?
Tetsuji Endo, Yasukawa's actor, was a regular in many detective series in the 90s. He also provided voices for Legend of the Galactic Heroes and Go Nagai's Scary Zone.
The jewel thieves are prolific in-suit actors for most of the 90s. Jiro Okamoto in particular is the actor for Fire, Knight Fire, Redder, Bill Goldy, Blue Beet, Gun Gibson, and Black Beet, among others!

Episode 48: A Huge Explosion at the Beetle Base?!

Rain has been falling for over a week since the battle against Dargryphon, hiding inside them a deadly surprise for humanity. Mother's ultimate plan is coming together and the Melzard forces launch their final attack on the B-Fighters. Will they be able to survive the onslaught of evil heading their way?

Episode 49: The Dawn of Earth's Destruction

Mother Melzard's plan is revealed and all of humanity is in danger. B-Fighter have very little help left, with their base destroyed, along with the Neo Beet Machines, their only plan of attack is to storm Melzard's base...

Episode 50: Last Battle

The final fight between the B-Fighters and Melzard begins. B-Fighter face down the remaining Melzard, with Jadow Motherla ready to destroy the planet. Can our heroes succeed in such overwhelming odds?

And that's it for B-Fighter Kabuto.

Til next time,

(Do read the Foreword+Background Trivia text that comes with the Subs!)

Greetings from the Gentlemen of Hàn!

This is our first english fansub release of the first 23 episodes (out of 84) of the 1994’s Romance of the Three Kingdoms.
It comprises of the first full arc of the series, titled “群雄逐鹿” or “Deer-Hunt of Lords”.

The 1994 Romance of the Three Kingdoms is a TV adaption of the novel Romance of the Three Kingdoms. The 1994 version is to this day considered one of the best Chinese historical television shows, being much more authentic and poetic than most adaptions of the novel, and adapting both the historical text, the Records of the Three Kingdoms, and the novel in a way that flows naturally, yet faithfully.

To this day it still ranks as the definitive take on Three Kingdoms, bar none.
We hope you enjoy our efforts into delivering this piece of media history, one most people are likely less knowledgeable on overall.

Please leave us a comment and support if you enjoy our efforts.

title: [Henshin-Man]Denjin Zaborger 1-4 (Hardsub)
description:
Here are episodes 1-4 of Denjin Zaborger, aka Electroid Zaborger, with full English subtitles.

I started this project while I was on You Tube and was approached by Fedda, my translator, who asked if he could help out with anything. I gave him Zaborger, since I had some raws for it and no one had really tried to sub it before.

The result of our collaboration were these four episodes, which feature Akira Yamaguchi (of Riderman fame) as Daimon Yutaka, a sort-of special agent/detective equipped with his late father's invention: the crime-fighting, transforming robot Denjin Zaborger. Zaborger actually turns into a motorcycle when not in robot mode, and Daimon rides this bike all over Japan, taking on Dr. Akunomiya and his "secret criminal organization," Sigma. Sigma is naturally armed with an plethora of mecha-borgs to battle Zaborger with, but with Daimon's voice-activated commands ("Zaborga! Chain Punch!") and Zaborger's superior tech, Daimon almost always came out on top.

The series was produced by P Productions, who also did Tiger Seven, Ambassador Magma, Spectreman, Condorman, and many other rare classics. This was their last series, and while it ran for an entire 52 episodes, the company closed its doors shortly after its completion, due to a slumping market for tokusatsu shows and several shows that had bombed before Zaborger's broadcast run.

Because these were originally posted to You Tube, they are hardsubbed, since soft subs aren't compatible with You Tube's code. I may re-do these as soft-sub MKVs in the future. This project is currently in limbo, and has been for a while, since Fedda went off to college and is far too busy to spend time translating anything, and no other translators have stepped forward to take his place.

I believe this may have been the only time someone successfully fansubbed Zaborger (and not just one ep, but four), so this is also a little bit of fansub history.

I hope you enjoy this classic blast from the tokusatsu past, and be sure to seed for as long as you can!

title: [Henshin-Man]Megaloman 01 (Softsub MKV)
description:
Here is the first episode of Megaloman, with full English subtitles that actually make sense! (gasp)

Seriously, I threw out what ARR/Kingmenu attempted to do a few years back and did my own translation & styling, with Kaiju doing the timing. The rest you’ll have to see for yourself.

Megaloman was produced by Toho in 1979 as a tokusatsu/giant hero series. It lasted 31 episodes before being canceled due to low ratings. It’s basically a clone of Ultraman with some sentai themes sprinkled in for good measure. The most notable feature of this series is the hero’s costume design, which has a long mane of blonde hair running down his back. This mane would catch on fire, stand straight up, and shoot a fireball at the kaiju of the week in order to defeat it. Gotta love 70’s toku!

This file is a softsub MKV, with subs styled in a way that mirrors an 80's VHS fansub. You have been warned.

I also apologize for the slight delay in uploading this as opposed to the hardsubbed version first; ISP was acting up.

Megaloman has never had an official VHS/DVD/BD release in Japan or anywhere else, so the raw is actually a VOD (Video on Demand) rip from an old broadcast VHS source. It’s not terrible, but the nighttime scenes are a little dark. These raws were shared via Google Drive on the Brazilian toku site Planet Satsus, so if you feel like spending an hour or two doing some DDLs, head over there and get them before they vanish forever.

This is still an active project, and I am working on translating episode 2, so stay tuned, and enjoy!

title: [Henshin-Man] Fuun Lion Maru 03 (576p)(AAC)(MKV)
description:
Here is episode 3 of Fuun Lion Maru, aka Storm Cloud Lion Maru, with full English subtitles.

The raw was ripped in 576p from the Portuguese ISOs. The fansub includes the Japanese audio track in an AAC format and is a softsub MKV. I won't be doing hardsubs for this series unless someone really needs them.

The original subtitle file & timing were done by Bycrosser way back in 2004. SFX Japan/Kaiju saved them all these years and passed them along after I made the raws. I re-timed Bycrosser's script and gave it a proper translation, since his subs were dubtitles based off the Portuguese dub.

This episode features a large tank shaped like a turtle's shell that is equipped with a flamethrower cannon. How this thing works and runs in feudal Japan is beyond me. Other vehicles equipped with deadly devices would appear in future episodes.

Hyoma, aka Black Jaguar, also makes an appearance here, and shows that he's only interested in money, prompting Sankichi to say "What a jerk!" 

Enjoy this rare slice of tokusatsu pie, and be sure to seed for as long as you're able!

### [Team ONIBE] Aqours ONLINE LoveLive! ~LOST WORLD~ [BD 1080p]

Time flies when you have nowhere to go, huh? It’s a little late, but we’re proud to present Aqours’ first online concert, LOST WORLD! title: [Henshin-Man] Jail Breakers (1976) (DVD)(MKV)
description:
I thought I'd take a page from Dodgy's book and upload an old Toei yakuza movie: the rare 1976 Sonny Chiba film, "Jail Breakers."

This is the old MovieTime release, which was ripped from the UK DVD edition of this film. It is restored & remastered, but not to the degree that we're used to seeing today, since the rip is so old. It is still a softsub mkv though, so it has that going for it, and the subtitles are professionally done, so that's another plus.

In this film, a group of mercenaries make a living by breaking rich convicts out of prison, getting paid to do it, and then turning them loose on the populous to pull their dirty deeds again. When the team of "jail breakers" attempts to bust out their latest quarry, Sonny Chiba hitches a ride on their helicopter, and they realize they've rescued the wrong guy! After several attempted double-crosses by Chiba, he agrees to pay off his debt to them by working alongside their group, which leads to more 1970's Toei-style action, gunfights, car chases, and the karate that Chiba was best known for. Chiba also gets a love interest in this one that he isn't sleeping with in the first 5 minutes, and the film's plot is extremely well-written and will keep you guessing as to who's going to double-cross who next.

"Jail Breakers" is nearly forgotten in the huge back catalog of movies that Sonny and Toei made in the 70's, but it is definitely worth seeing at least once for fans of Chiba and fans of Toei Yakuza movies.

Enjoy this rare piece of Japanese cinematic history, and be sure to seed for a while after you're done!

description:
![Zenkai Bean Theater](https://i.imgur.com/1c5yfTY.png)

https://bistrotjurer.wordpress.com/2022/02/05/kikai-sentai-zenkaiger-zenkai-bean-theater-episodes-1-6-8-11/

Zenryoku Zenkai! We've got a little surprise for you all here!

Zenkai Bean Theater is a set of twelve shorts that come with the Blu-Rays for Zenkaiger starring these tiny stuffed dolls of the Zenkaiger characters. These episodes are comedy shorts between two to five minutes, each.

These episodes are super funny and adorable. I just love looking at these cute little beans and hearing their cute sound effects. It's just a great time. If you're a fan of Zenkaiger, then you have to check this out.

Episodes 1, 8 and 11 were released a few months ago on TTFC as a promotion for the Blu-Ray sets and for Super Hero Senki, and episodes 1-6 were released with the first two Blu-Ray sets. We will continue to release these as the Blu-Ray sets come out.

Zenkaiger has quickly become one of my favorite (if not my absolute favorite) toku series. It's been a blast to watch, and I love that I have the opportunity to make this fun extra series available to everyone.

Shoutouts to AMeanMotorScooter of Berndadelta Subs for translating, as well as to Ei for the TTFC raws and ZichzMaster for the Blu-Ray raws. Also, welcome to alpacathunder1, who joined our team as a timer! He timed episodes 4-6, and is taking over timing for HadoGumi starting with episode 27. (That's still coming, trust me!)

Episodes 1-3, 8, 11
Azurillkirby: Timing Eps 1-3 + 8 + 11, QC
alpacathunder1: Timing Eps 4-6
AMeanMotorScooter: Translation

Notes:
-Episodes 1, 8, and 11 all had previews for the upcoming episodes on the TTFC release. Episodes 3 and 6 each have preview for the next 3 episodes that would be in the next set. The Blu-Ray versions of episodes 1, 2, 4, and 5 have no preview. Because we're using the Blu-Ray raw for episode 1, we've added the ep 2 preview from the web version as an additional file.
-Episodes 1, 8, and 11 also all had previews for Super Hero Senki on the TTFC release. While we didn't sub the Senki preview, we kept it in the videos for eps 8 and 11.

- This is a remux, in this instance meaning we pulled the movie as-is off the 4K disk. It was not re-encoded.
- As some of the primary players people use these days cannot handle SSA in-client and will even attempt to transcode HDR video (a nightmare of a processor hit and extremely slow and damaging), we've provided our first PGS sub. We did our best with this, it's still a learning process and we had to pare down a lot of the formatting niceties to get it to look acceptable.
- The original SSA track is also included if your client can handle it.
- As with the 1080p release, this is based off of XIG's sub of the movie. Content-wise, it is almost identical to our original scrub, no major changes.

title: [Henshin-Man] Captain Ultra - Episode 01 (480p h265 HEVC)
description:
Here is a fansub/scrub of Toei's 1967 sci-fi tokusatsu series "Captain Ultra," for which I used Toei Tokusatsu World's subs (via downsub.com) and re-timed them to chuby's h265 raw, while editing the subs for some of the words they missed and some of the things that just didn't fit. 

"Captain Ultra" was a filler series that aired right after "Ultraman" ended, so the network only ordered 24 episodes, and boy, did this thing end way too soon. It sort-of plays like a mix of "Star Trek," "Godzilla," and "Lost In Space," considering one of Ultra's teammates is a robot with claws for hands (and a bazooka arm!). It's all 1960's sci-fi schlock, but sometimes you need that, since sci-fi and space exploration was all the rage in the 60's, and scientists were still making discoveries about the universe; now it seems like all they have to tell us is that the world is doomed.

In any case, enjoy this sub/scrub of Captain Ultra's first episode (and episode two is on the way, hopefully sooner rather than later), and be sure to seed for a while after you're done!

description:

(Do read the Foreword+Background Trivia text that comes with the Subs!)

Greetings from the Gentlemen of Hàn!

This is our second English fansub batch release of **_Episodes 24 to 31_** of the _**1994’s Romance of the Three Kingdoms.**_ This is the part 1 of the 2nd arc of the series, titled _**“赤壁鏖战”**_ or _**“Battle of Red Cliffs”.**_  
To lighten our workload and getting more episodes available, we've cut the 2nd Arc of the series into parts.  
This is part 1, introducing Ya Boy **Zhuge Liang**, one of The Most Iconic Characters of not just Three Kingdoms, but of Chinese history and culture in general. A representative of the very [East-Asian character archetype of Strategist Genius](https://youtube.com/watch?v=P6C4AEkzb6o), whom gave us many a works of tactical intrigue and mind-games, from literature to even anime and video games.
Works like Legend of Galactic Heroes, Heroic Legend of Arslan, Berserk, Suikoden series, and Code Geass just to name a few obvious examples would not exist as they are without the many tactics of Zhuge Liang!

 
We hope you enjoy the translation. Please leave us a comment and support if you enjoy our efforts

description:
![Zenkai Bean Theater](https://i.imgur.com/1c5yfTY.png)

https://bistrotjurer.wordpress.com/2022/02/05/kikai-sentai-zenkaiger-zenkai-bean-theater-episodes-1-6-8-11/

Zenryoku Zenkai! We've got a little surprise for you all here!

Zenkai Bean Theater is a set of twelve shorts that come with the Blu-Rays for Zenkaiger starring these tiny stuffed dolls of the Zenkaiger characters. These episodes are comedy shorts between two to five minutes, each.

These episodes are super funny and adorable. I just love looking at these cute little beans and hearing their cute sound effects. It's just a great time. If you're a fan of Zenkaiger, then you have to check this out.

Episodes 1, 8 and 11 were released a few months ago on TTFC as a promotion for the Blu-Ray sets and for Super Hero Senki, and episodes 1-6 were released with the first two Blu-Ray sets. We will continue to release these as the Blu-Ray sets come out.

Zenkaiger has quickly become one of my favorite (if not my absolute favorite) toku series. It's been a blast to watch, and I love that I have the opportunity to make this fun extra series available to everyone.

Shoutouts to AMeanMotorScooter of Berndadelta Subs for translating, as well as to Ei for the TTFC raws and ZichzMaster for the Blu-Ray raws. Also, welcome to alpacathunder1, who joined our team as a timer! He timed episodes 4-6, and is taking over timing for HadoGumi starting with episode 27. (That's still coming, trust me!)

Episodes 1-3, 8, 11
Azurillkirby: Timing Eps 1-3 + 8 + 11, QC
alpacathunder1: Timing Eps 4-6
AMeanMotorScooter: Translation

Notes:
-Episodes 1, 8, and 11 all had previews for the upcoming episodes on the TTFC release. Episodes 3 and 6 each have preview for the next 3 episodes that would be in the next set. The Blu-Ray versions of episodes 1, 2, 4, and 5 have no preview. Because we're using the Blu-Ray raw for episode 1, we've added the ep 2 preview from the web version as an additional file.
-Episodes 1, 8, and 11 also all had previews for Super Hero Senki on the TTFC release. While we didn't sub the Senki preview, we kept it in the videos for eps 8 and 11.

title: [Henshin-Man] Yakuza Deka (1970)(DVD)(MKV)
description:
Here's a rare(ish) Toei gangster film starring Sonny Chiba: "Yakuza Deka," or Gangster Cop, from way back in 1970.

This rip was taken from the remastered UK DVD version of this film, and so are the soft subs. The subs are a vobsub rip from the DVD and were encoded in .idx and .sub, so I muxed them into the video the way they were. They don't look great, but they're there, and it's a professional translation, so that's what counts.

This film takes the old Yojimbo story (where the samurai plays the two feuding clans off each other) and swaps it to a modern-day urban setting, with Chiba playing the resident gangster who is switching between Yakuza clans and pitting them against each other. The other side of this coin is that he's actually an undercover cop, and Chiba shows why he's one of the best Japan ever had as he uses his high karate to mow through gangsters and cops alike. When his cover's blown, he goes on full offense, and the final car/jeep chase through Toei's trademark gravel pit is really something to see. Plus, Sonny actually tries to sing the opening song, which will either make you laugh out loud or make you grind your teeth in utter agony. 

 If you like the old Toei yakuza movies, and you liked my previous upload of "Jail Breakers," then you'll love "Yakuza Deka," and be sure to seed for a while after you're done!

It's an exciting escape full of twists, turns, and betrayals as Kosaku and the informant flee certain death from a well armed Mafia group.
